I felt like I let my weight REALLY, like REALLY get to me for the first time. I say this all to say that no matter how strong and positive you are, everyone struggles with bad body image. I decided to post this picture anyways and remind myself of how much good I‚Äôm doing my body and how grateful I am that I don‚Äôt have to deal with a crazy appetite anymore. In the end, this will all be worth it. And if you‚Äôre struggling right now, you‚Äôre not alone...trust me üôè‚ô•Ô∏è #allin

Body neutral...

Since I‚Äôve been in Canada, I‚Äôve been focusing on reconnecting with @jeffnippard as well as focusing on me and my mental health. I‚Äôve expressed my struggles with the pressure I‚Äôve been feeling lately on social media... that is likely fabricated in my own mind, but nonetheless still weighs heavily on me. I feel this constant pressure to make sure I‚Äôm setting a good example by loving my body no matter what, but I‚Äôm human and it‚Äôs just not the case.
